  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Photograph</ab>
      <ab subtype="creation" type="lido:event">
        <date>1939-1943</date>
      </ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The photograph shows the exterior of the ‘Gloria’ cinema in the Albanian seaport of Durrës in approximately 1940. The facade consists of four entrances and a canopied box office. In front of the neighbouring building, a movie is being advertised. The slogan ‘A fascist regime is a fair regime’ is displayed on the upper part of the wall.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The inserted name ‘Luce’ (an Italian film and photo production company) indicates that the photograph was taken during the Italian occupation of Albania between 1939 and 1943.</ab>
